  #page-content.page-sa
    section#hero.hero-auto
      .page-title.wrapper
        #wolf-title.wolf-grid.clearfix
          .wolf-item.wfull.wright.wolf-text(data-speed='2')
            .wolf-item-inner
              .wolf-media
                img(src='img/sa/sa_01-medium.jpg' srcset="img/sa/sa_01-small.jpg 640w, img/sa/sa_01-medium.jpg 800w, img/sa/sa_01-large.jpg 1800w" alt='Success Academy Classroom')
              .wolf-caption.ctop(style='width:60%;')
                h5.alttitle Front-End Development
                h1
                  strong Success Academy
    section#page-body.nopadding
      .wrapper-small
        h6
          strong Project Details
        p Success Academy is a network of world-class charter schools across New York City. They also serve as a catalyst and national model for education reform through their writing platform, Mission Possible. SA asked Makeable to help show off their creative instructional approach by updating their website. Our work allowed them to highlight every school in their network, establish a platform for generating interest in education reform, and provide e-commerace capabilities for events and extracurricular activities. I developed the entire front-end and in-browser interaction design and implemented the Google Maps API, several social network APIs, and used HTML5's Canvas for graphs across the site. The whole site was finished in two weeks in hyper-agile workflow with the visual designer, 
          a(href='http://www.stompsondesign.com/' target='_blank') Dr. Sara S. Thompson.
